# Vue Finish Checklist

Before finishing Vue work, verify:

- [ ] Behavior matches requirements
- [ ] Source state is minimal; derived values use `computed`
- [ ] SFC order is script → template → style; templates stay declarative
- [ ] Components are focused; split when multi-responsibility
- [ ] App/page/route views stay composition surfaces (not full feature dumps)
- [ ] Props/emits (and inject keys) are explicit and typed
- [ ] Stateful/side-effect logic lives in composables when justified
- [ ] Optional Vue features used only when required
- [ ] Performance tweaks applied only after core behavior works
- [ ] No `server/` routes or runtime Nitro APIs introduced
- [ ] New pages are prerenderable (`NuxtLink` or listed in prerender routes)
- [ ] SEO meta set for public pages (`useSeoMeta` / `useHead`)
